50|$|Internal risks {{arise from}} factors (endogenous variables, {{which can be}} controlled) such as human factors (talent management, strikes), {{technological}} factors (emerging technologies), physical factors (failure of machines, fire or theft), operational factors (access to credit, cost cutting, advertisement). External risks arise from factors (exogenous variables, which cannot be controlled) such as economic factors (<b>market</b> <b>risks,</b> pricing pressure), natural factors (floods, earthquakes), political factors (compliance and regulations of government).|$|E
